<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-07-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-07-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="1022" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1022">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.48/3241</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Consul <persName type="to">Guyant</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-07-01">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 1, 1916</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>You are authorized to arrange for feeding surplus refugees mentioned in
                            your telegram yesterday. After detention period, deliver Porto Ricans to
                            Immigration Station, where they will be held until they can be sent to
                            Porto Rico.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>